  "packageName": "@cubid/web3",
  "readme": [
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "# "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/web3`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\nLegacy shared-wallet Cubid compatibility package for older installs that still\ndepend on the pre-split wallet surface.\n\n## When To Choose This Package\n\nPrefer "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/evm`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for new EVM integrations, "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/wagmi`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for\nwagmi-specific React integrations, "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/near`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for new NEAR integrations,\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/polkadot`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for new Polkadot integrations, "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/aptos`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for new\nAptos integrations, "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/solana`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for new Solana integrations, "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/sui`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\nfor new Sui integrations, "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/cardano`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for new Cardano integrations,\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/bitcoin`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for new Bitcoin integrations, "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/starknet`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for new\nStarknet integrations, "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/stellar`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for new Stellar integrations,\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/tezos`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for new Tezos integrations, and "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/cosmos`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for new Cosmos\nintegrations. Use "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/web3`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " only when you still depend on the older shared\nwallet surface. New chain-specific work should prefer the dedicated chain\npackages instead of expanding this shared surface.\n\n## Install\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "```sh\nnpm install @cubid/web3 @cubid/core\n```"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n## Registry Availability\n\n- npm: supported\n- JSR: not published by policy\n\n## Maintenance Status\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/web3`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " is now a frozen compatibility package.\n\n- The supported shared-wallet surface is intentionally limited to the existing\n  "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`evm`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": ", "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`near`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": ", "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`near-wallet`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": ", and "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`solana`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " stamp families.\n- New chain-specific helpers and new chain families should land only in their\n  dedicated packages.\n- If "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/web3`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " ever needs another release, treat it as a manual\n  compatibility exception rather than a normal forward-looking package update.\n\n## API Reference\n\n- JSON reference: "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`../../docs/reference/api/web3.json`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n- Package matrix: "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`../../README.md`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n## Capability Metadata\n\nThe legacy wallet surface preserves optional "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`capabilities`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " metadata on\nconnections and verification results. Use that metadata for features such as\nsmart accounts, session keys, paymasters, or gas sponsorship instead of\nassuming every wallet connection supports them.\n\nThe package exports "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`getCubidWalletCapabilities(...)`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " and\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`hasCubidWalletCapability(...)`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " to keep those checks explicit while the chain\nsplit continues."
    }
  ]
}
